### Handle validation errors with try-catch in Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/basics.mdx

Catches ZodError instances thrown by .parse() and accesses the issues array containing detailed validation error information including expected types, error codes, paths, and messages.

```typescript
try {
  Player.parse({ username: 42, xp: "100" });
} catch(error){
  if(error instanceof z.ZodError){
    error.issues;
    /* [
      {
        expected: 'string',
        code: 'invalid_type',
        path: [ 'username' ],
        message: 'Invalid input: expected string'
      },
      {
        expected: 'number',
        code: 'invalid_type',
        path: [ 'xp' ],
        message: 'Invalid input: expected number'
      }
    ] */
  }
}
```

```typescript
try {
  Player.parse({ username: 42, xp: "100" });
} catch(error){
  if(error instanceof z.core.$ZodError){
    error.issues;
    /* [
      {
        expected: 'string',
        code: 'invalid_type',
        path: [ 'username' ],
        message: 'Invalid input: expected string'
      },
      {
        expected: 'number',
        code: 'invalid_type',
        path: [ 'xp' ],
        message: 'Invalid input: expected number'
      }
    ] */
  }
}
```

