### Handling Zod Validation Errors with ZodError (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

This example demonstrates how to check for validation failures using `safeParse` and access the `issues` array within a `ZodError` object. The `issues` array provides detailed information about validation problems, including error codes, expected/received types, and paths to invalid fields.

```ts
const result = z
  .object({
    name: z.string(),
  })
  .safeParse({ name: 12 });

if (!result.success) {
  result.error.issues;
  /* [
      {
        "code": "invalid_type",
        "expected": "string",
        "received": "number",
        "path": [ "name" ],
        "message": "Expected string, received number"
      }
  ] */
}
```

