### Flattening Zod Validation Errors in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/ERROR_HANDLING.md

Demonstrates how to use the `.flatten()` method on a Zod error object to get a simplified, single-level error structure, grouping field-specific errors and root-level form errors. This is useful when the schema is not deeply nested and provides clear separation of errors.

```typescript
if (!result.success) {
  console.log(result.error.flatten());
}
/*
  {
    formErrors: [],
    fieldErrors: {
      name: ['Expected string, received null'],
      contactInfo: ['Invalid email']
    },
  }
*/
```

```typescript
const result = FormData.safeParse(null);
if (!result.success) {
  result.error.flatten();
  /*  
    {
      formErrors: ["Invalid input: expected object, received null"],
      fieldErrors: {}
    }  
  */
}
```

