### Handle Zod Parsing Errors with Static `catch` Value

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Demonstrates using Zod's `.catch()` method to provide a static fallback value in case of a parsing error. If the schema validation fails, the specified catch value is returned instead of throwing an error.

```ts
const numberWithCatch = z.number().catch(42);

numberWithCatch.parse(5); // => 5
numberWithCatch.parse("tuna"); // => 42
```

