### Handle Zod validation results using safeParse in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/README.md

This example shows how to use the `.safeParse()` method to avoid `try/catch` blocks for validation. It returns a discriminated union result object, allowing you to check `result.success` and access either `result.data` (parsed value) or `result.error` (ZodError instance) for convenient error handling.

```ts
const result = Player.safeParse({ username: 42, xp: "100" });
if (!result.success) {
  result.error; // ZodError instance
} else {
  result.data; // { username: string; xp: number }
}
```

