### Format ZodError for Structured Output

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/ERROR_HANDLING.md

Illustrates the use of the `.format()` method on a `ZodError` object to transform the flat `issues` array into a nested object structure. This formatted output denormalizes errors by field, making it easier to integrate with UI components for displaying validation messages.

```ts
if (!result.success) {
  console.log(result.error.format());
  /*
    {
      name: {
        _errors: ['Expected string, received null']
      },
      contactInfo: {
        email: {
          _errors: ['Invalid email']
        }
      }
    }
  */
}
```

