### Implement Custom Zod Error Map for Message Customization in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/ERROR_HANDLING.md

This TypeScript code defines a `ZodErrorMap` to customize validation error messages. It demonstrates how to override messages for specific issue codes like `invalid_type` and `custom`, falling back to Zod's default message for other errors. This allows for tailored and user-friendly error reporting.

```ts
import { z } from "zod";

const customErrorMap: z.ZodErrorMap = (issue, ctx) => {
  if (issue.code === z.ZodIssueCode.invalid_type) {
    if (issue.expected === "string") {
      return { message: "bad type!" };
    }
  }
  if (issue.code === z.ZodIssueCode.custom) {
    return { message: `less-than-${(issue.params || {}).minimum}` };
  }
  return { message: ctx.defaultError };
};

z.setErrorMap(customErrorMap);
```

