### Parse String and Handle ZodError - Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/error-customization.mdx

Demonstrates using safeParse() to validate a string schema and access the ZodError issues array. Returns a result object with success flag and error details containing code, path, and message properties.

```typescript
import * as z from "zod";

const result = z.string().safeParse(12); // { success: false, error: ZodError }
result.error.issues;
// [
//   {
//     expected: 'string',
//     code: 'invalid_type',
//     path: [],
//     message: 'Invalid input: expected string, received number'
//   }
// ]
```

