### Customize Per-Parse Error Messages in Zod (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/error-customization.mdx

Provide a custom error function directly to the `.safeParse()` or `.parse()` method's options to handle specific validation issue types. The `iss` object's `code` property allows discrimination between different error causes, offering fine-grained control over messages for individual validation calls. This method takes precedence over global error maps.

```typescript
const result = schema.safeParse(12, {
  error: (iss) => {
    if (iss.code === "invalid_type") {
      return `invalid type, expected ${iss.expected}`;
    }
    if (iss.code === "too_small") {
      return `minimum is ${iss.minimum}`;
    }
    // ...
  }
})
```
